<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph box="[0,1876,90,2695]" pageId="16" pageNumber="269" type="mainText">
Annual herb with caducous leaves. Flowers bisexual, sometimes staminate, solitary or 2-3 in clusters, these in panicles; perianth lobes 5, connate up to the middle; fruiting perianth winged, enclosing the fruit; stamens 5; ovary covered by a fleece of hairs; stigmas 2. Pericarp membranous, free; seeds horizontal; embryo annular; radicle centrifugal. 2/1 =36. One sp., 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Cycloloma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="269" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atriplicifolium">
C. atriplicifolium 
<authority>(Sprengel) J.Coulter</authority>
</taxonomicName>
, W and C N America, adventive in Europe and S America.
</paragraph>
